My favorite dim sum place in Oakland. It gets really busy from ~11:30 to 1pm but you can get seated quicker if you're willing to share a large table with other diners. The food is good, and the prices are fantastic. The only downside to this place is that it can be difficult to order if you don't speak Cantonese.

However, their prices are very fair and their dim sum is pretty good. Nothing to die for, but definitely satisfies your dim sum cravings.
